    <div class="container">
        <section class="about-section">
            <h2>Our Story</h2>
            <p>ParentShopper was born from a simple frustration: too many parenting product reviews that felt like marketing copy, not real parent experiences.</p>
            
            <p>As parents ourselves, we've been through the overwhelming process of choosing the right products for our children. We've bought things that seemed perfect in reviews but didn't work for our real-life situations. We've wasted money on products that promised everything but delivered little.</p>
            
            <p>That's why we created ParentShopper - to cut through the noise and give you honest, practical advice from parents who've actually used these products in real-world situations.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="about-section">
            <h2>Our Approach</h2>
            <div class="approach-grid">
                <div class="approach-item">
                    <h3>Real Parent Experiences</h3>
                    <p>Every recommendation comes from actual parent experiences, not marketing departments. We test products in real homes with real children.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="approach-item">
                    <h3>Honest Reviews</h3>
                    <p>We tell you what works, what doesn't, and what's worth your money. No product is perfect, and we're honest about limitations.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="approach-item">
                    <h3>Research-Based</h3>
                    <p>When we don't have personal experience, we research extensively, analyzing hundreds of parent reviews and expert opinions.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="approach-item">
                    <h3>Time-Saving</h3>
                    <p>We know you're busy. Our reviews get straight to the point, helping you make decisions quickly and confidently.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

